## Architecture overview (new model)

```
Director's laptop — Tauri desktop app
  ├── FastAPI sidecar (uvicorn, local port)
  │     ├── CP-SAT solver (OR-Tools, unchanged)
  │     ├── SQLite via SQLAlchemy (source of truth)
  │     └── Sync service → Supabase Postgres (when online)
  │
  └── Tauri WebView (React frontend)
        └── Talks to local FastAPI only

Operators / assistants — browser on any device
  └── Talk to Supabase directly (read via REST/Realtime)
        └── Write actions → local FastAPI via internet
              (director's machine must be reachable)

Public TV display — Vercel
  └── Reads Supabase Realtime (read-only, no auth required)

Supabase
  ├── Auth (identity for all users)
  ├── Postgres (cloud mirror of SQLite — not primary)
  └── Realtime (broadcasts writes to operators and TV)
```

**Do not relitigate this model.** Fly.io, Render, and a standalone
cloud FastAPI host are explicitly removed. FastAPI runs only on the
director's machine.

