## Step B — Solver locking

The CP-SAT solver must never reassign a locked match. This is a
surgical addition to `scheduler_core/` — do not restructure anything
else in that package.

### B1 — ScheduleRequest extension

Add one field to `ScheduleRequest` in
`scheduler_core/domain/models.py`:

```python
@dataclass
class LockedAssignment:
    match_id: str
    court_id: str
    time_slot: int   # same unit as existing time slots

@dataclass
class ScheduleRequest:
    # ... existing fields unchanged ...
    locked_assignments: list[LockedAssignment] = field(default_factory=list)
```

This is additive. No existing field changes. No existing caller breaks
because `locked_assignments` defaults to empty.

### B2 — Solver constraint

In `scheduler_core/engine/cpsat_backend.py`, add one method:

```python
def _add_locked_constraints(
    self,
    model: cp_model.CpModel,
    locked: list[LockedAssignment],
    court_vars: dict,
    time_vars: dict,
) -> None:
    """Fix court and time for every locked match before solving."""
    for assignment in locked:
        mid = assignment.match_id
        if mid not in court_vars or mid not in time_vars:
            # Match not in this solve scope — skip silently
            continue
        model.Add(court_vars[mid] == self._court_index(assignment.court_id))
        model.Add(time_vars[mid] == assignment.time_slot)
```

Call `_add_locked_constraints` in the solve method immediately before
`model.Solve(...)`. It must be called after all other constraints are
added so nothing can override the locks.

Do not modify any other method in `cpsat_backend.py`.

